Your leaders in their wisdom will have chosen a set that matter in your organisation, and that can measure your overall prowess. You will now be rated by others on these, and the ideal employee is expected to score highly across all competencies. The best people are supposed to be well-rounded, you see. 

If you score highly across the board you become a candidate for promotion. If you have gaps, your learning needs will be recorded and training programmes recommended. It all seems to be very robust and scientific. 



